  "2026-05-27T18:34:27.792Z",maintainer-agent,"Opened PR #77 (perf/cache-health-drift-startup): metadata body-split cache, skip-unchanged cache writes, onRead short-circuit, cached with-body path (removed dead listAllDocuments), drift verification cache (health 8.4s->1.3s), and advisory telemetry health warnings (ok:false fix). Closes pm-4r5t + pm-1lgy. All local gates green: 1852 tests, 100% coverage, typecheck, static/docs-skills, secrets, changelog. Awaiting CI + AI bot review."
  "2026-05-27T19:08:33.696Z",maintainer-agent,"PR #77 merged to main (merge commit 3a85a060) after full green CI (build, compat/smokes/static/typecheck/coverage gates, runtime matrix macos+ubuntu Node 20/22/24) and AI bot review. Addressed CodeRabbit+Codex P2 findings in follow-up 42cfead6: drift-cache key now includes ctime_ms; --strict-exit help clarified (gates on ok, advisory telemetry excluded); onRead hook warnings surfaced. Sourcery was rate-limited (non-blocking). Shipped: pm list 401->310ms, pm health 8.4s->1.3s, health ok:true. Closed pm-4r5t + pm-1lgy; follow-ups pm-edge/xzrx/7ilo/1b96/fl0c remain open under this epic."
  "2026-05-27T22:27:17.814Z",maintainer-agent,"Session 2026-05-28: opened branch feat/agent-ux-compact-output-and-mutation-guards to close two epic children as ONE coherent agent-UX + token-efficiency PR (the user's critical priority). Scope: pm-edge (create-type mistype guard; compact validate output via required_fields-only per-field ID arrays; dedupe search/list filters block to stop emitting projection.fields twice) + pm-fl0c (test --add inline-env wording; depends_on dep-kind alias->blocked_by; surface same-command nearest-flag did-you-mean in human output — verified MISSING on current build for 'pm create --titel'; plan materialize skip completed/already-materialized steps; close inline --resolution/--expected/--actual; scaffold uses install-safe typed extension shape). Deferred to follow-up PRs: pm-7ilo (model-agnostic search config), pm-xzrx (calendar), pm-1b96 (refactors), pm-ss1d (esbuild bundling). Three specialized sub-agents own disjoint file sets to avoid conflicts."
  "2026-05-28T05:12:34.893Z",maintainer-agent,"Session 2026-05-28 (cont): closed pm-edge + pm-fl0c on feat/agent-ux-compact-output-and-mutation-guards in a single PR. 8 fixes: (1) create-type guard refuses pm create Epic with no title via PmCliError(create_positional_type_without_title), (2) validate metadata details emit counts/item_ids only for active required_fields (~150 redundant lines/run gone on minimal preset), (3) list/search filters block dropped duplicated projection.{mode,fields}, (4) OSA Damerau-Levenshtein in core/shared/levenshtein.ts (adjacent transposition cost 1) — fixes both bootstrap-args auto-correct AND commander-usage flag-typo hints; affects scoreCommandPathMatch too, (5) test --add wording now says INLINE in the command string with example, (6) --dep kind=depends_on accepted as canonical blocked_by alias on update + dep-remove, (7) plan materialize idempotent — resolveMaterializeTargets returns {targets, skipped}; new PlanCommandResult.materialize_skipped, (8) pm close --resolution/--expected-result/--actual-result inline (+snake aliases) applied pre-validation so one call satisfies --validate-close strict, (B-1) scaffold emits defineExtension import + wrapper matching docs. New tests: levenshtein.spec.ts (post-loop-guard branch via abcd/abcyy@1), plan/close/update/scaffold/help-runtime positive coverage. Gates: 1866 tests, 100% coverage (stmt/branch/func/line), typecheck, quality:static, quality:docs-skills, security:scan. PR pending. Follow-ups (deferred): pm-1b96 refactors, pm-7ilo model-agnostic search, pm-xzrx calendar, pm-ss1d esbuild bundling."
  "2026-05-28T05:15:20.768Z",maintainer-agent,"PR #78 opened — https://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/pull/78 (feat/agent-ux-compact-output-and-mutation-guards -> main). +550/-65. State: OPEN MERGEABLE. Bot reviews triggered (@codex, /gemini review, @gemini-code-assist, @coderabbitai, @sourcery-ai). Waiting 20 minutes for CI + bot feedback per workflow."
  "2026-05-28T05:44:07.384Z",maintainer-agent,"PR #78 first bot pass landed (CI fully green 13/13). Addressing actionable findings: Codex P2 #1 — scaffold defineExtension import would ERR_MODULE_NOT_FOUND in extension-only mode (no package.json with the dep); split to typed shape for package mode and import-free + JSDoc @param shape for extension-only mode. Codex P2 #2 — added --resolution/--expected-result/--actual-result (with snake aliases) to CLOSE_FLAG_CONTRACTS so pm contracts/JSON help/bootstrap normalization surface them. Gemini high #1+#2 — defensive optional-chain guards in validate buildMetadataCheck (counts + item_ids loops) so a future custom required_field never throws TypeError. Gemini medium (idempotency) — pm plan materialize --steps all now returns a successful no-op (exit 0) with materialize_skipped populated when every selected step is already done, instead of throwing NOT_FOUND. Gemini medium (simplify) — dropped redundant trimmed.length===0 check in normalizeDependencyKindInput. CodeRabbit's 7 \"don't edit .agents/pm files\" comments: skipped — pm IS the system of record AND tracks these files in git (the entire pm-cli design). Sourcery shape-dedup: nice-to-have, deferred. 1866 tests, 100% coverage, all gates green. Re-triggering reviews."
  "2026-05-28T06:05:27.463Z",maintainer-agent,"PR #78 merged to main (merge commit a7ac69be) after second CI pass: 13/13 green, mergeStateStatus CLEAN. All actionable bot findings addressed in b3facfcd (Codex P2 #1 scaffold standalone-safe, Codex P2 #2 close inline contracts, Gemini high x2 validate guards, Gemini medium idempotent materialize, Gemini medium dep-kind helper). CodeRabbit's 7 \".agents/pm files\" comments confirmed false-positive (pm = system of record AND tracked in git). Sourcery shape-dedup deferred. Closed: pm-edge + pm-fl0c. Filed during session: pm-ydkl (pm comments --add HTML-escapes angle brackets). Follow-ups still open under this epic: pm-1b96 (refactors), pm-7ilo (model-agnostic search), pm-xzrx (calendar), pm-ss1d (esbuild bundling)."
  "2026-05-28T06:27:08.373Z",maintainer-agent,"PR #79 merged (d6858688) — chore/record-pr-78-merge-evidence applied via fast-forward. PR #79 review pass: sourcery looks great, gemini-code-assist x2 'no feedback', codex 'no major issues', coderabbit rate-limited (non-blocking — same pattern as prior PRs, no required-check failure). 12/12 CI green. Both PRs (#78 code + #79 evidence) now on main. Closing the session: pm-edge + pm-fl0c done; pm-th6y epic kept open for remaining children (pm-1b96, pm-7ilo, pm-xzrx, pm-ss1d)."
  "2026-05-28T16:41:23.271Z",maintainer-agent,"Session 2026-05-28 round 2 — merged PR #81 (commit 820d7322 on main) closing pm-ydkl + pm-9r7z (Fixed), pm-7ilo + pm-xzrx (Added), pm-1b96 (Changed). Companion fix in pm-changelog repo: PR #19 (commit 4fc0f0f) corrected the classifier so Issues containing CLI flag tokens (--add etc.) route to Fixed not Added. Four review rounds with codex / coderabbit / sourcery / gemini — all converged green with no remaining findings. Two follow-up items filed (pm-1lws for --expected/--add-tags alias inconsistency). All 1949 unit + integration tests pass at 100% coverage; pm health green; sentry shows no new errors in last 1h; telemetry enabled and draining."
  "2026-05-29T00:27:49.573Z",maintainer-agent,"Session 2026-05-29: opened branch feat/agent-ux-tag-mutations-and-result-aliases closing epic child pm-1lws (agent-UX flag-parity). Shipped: (1) --expected/--actual short aliases on pm update + create + update-many (matching pm close); (2) additive tag mutations --add-tags (create/update/update-many) + --remove-tags (update/update-many) via core/item/parse.ts helpers; (3) FIXED a real update-many bug where additive-tag-only updates were silently skipped (buildPlannedItemDiff ignored add/remove tag ops) — added buildTagMutationPlan replicating runUpdate's replace->add->remove order; (4) completed close completion section (was missing ALL inline closure flags). Wired contracts/MCP/docs/zsh+fish completions. 2 specialized sub-agents (docs + completion). 1973 tests, 100% coverage, all gates green. Companion: pm-changelog PR #20 (pmc-874d) fixes classifier command-name-keyword collision (Issues titled 'pm update ...' were misfiled Changed→now Fixed); also upgraded vendored pm-changelog extension 2026.5.27-1->2026.5.29."
  "2026-05-29T02:57:42.117Z",maintainer-agent,"Session 2026-05-29 COMPLETE: PR #82 merged (1174a12d) closing epic child pm-1lws. 5 review rounds, all bot feedback resolved (codex converged, gemini's final defensive/style suggestions declined with documented reasoning). Companion pm-changelog PR #20 merged (classifier strong/weak signal split + non-string type guard; pmc-874d). Final manual test on merged main: create/update/update-many/close all apply --add-tags/--remove-tags/--expected/--actual correctly incl. JSON-array argv + case-insensitive removal. pm health ok. Remaining open epic children: pm-ss1d (esbuild bundling), pm-59gj (package ecosystem) — both large standalone features, deferred."
